summary:
Joined ING Bank in 2020 in the Management & Reporting Analytics department, being responsible for the Standardize & Innovate Analytics projects in the Data & Analytics product area. Previously worked at Arthur Andersen, Deloitte, Alma Tourism, Novabase, CapGemini, Bring Global and PWC, assuming relevant roles.

Consultancy experience through the participation of a large number of projects in several sectors (Banking, Insurance, Energy, Government & Public Services and Life Sciences & Health Care) and in several geographies.

Wide experience in implementing Business Analytics, Information Management solutions and consulting services projects as well as architecture of solutions mainly focused on Digital Transformation, IoT, IT Strategy, Big Data, Predictive Modeling, Machine Learning and Analytics.

Extensive participation in HR processes such as recruitment, training, counseling, competencies, environment, resource scheduling, performance and talent management, as well as projects and services offers development such as employee experience, employee journey and HR dashboards.

• Master degree in Computer Science from the NOVA School of Science and Technology (Universidade NOVA de Lisboa);
• Degree in Computer Science from the Faculty of Sciences of the University of Lisbon;
• Certified consultant in project management (PMP level C) by APOGEP / IPMA;
• Several certifications in the Management, Leadership and Technical fields (PSPO II; PSPO I; PSM I; ITIL).

• Languages: Portuguese (native), English (proficient), Spanish (intermediate) and French (basic).

• Geographies (people and country): Angola, Australia, Chile, England, France, Ghana, Ireland, Italy, Mozambique, Netherlands, Nigeria, Norway, Oman, Portugal, Spain and USA.

Technical skills:
• Analytics: Google Cloud, Microstrategy, Microsoft Power BI, Tableau, Qlikview, Microsoft Reporting Services, Microsoft Analysis Services, OBIEE, SAS, Crystal Reports, Roambi, IBM Cognos, SAP Business Objects;
• Database: Greenplum, SQL Server, Microsoft Access, Oracle, MySQL, Sybase IQ, Toad, Erwin; SQLite.
• Data integration: Alteryx, IBM Data Stage, IBM Quality Stage, MS Integration Services, Alteryx; SAS;
• Programing: C, C#, C++,HTML,PL SQL,Visual Basic, .Net,XML,XSL,VBA,Java,Java Script, ASP,ASPX,Pascal,Clipper,Assembly,COBOL,ABAP 4,Python;
• Productivity: GitLab,Azure DevOps,ServiceNow,Slack,Jira,Microsoft Excel,Microsoft PowerPoint,Microsoft Project,Microsoft Word,Microsoft Sharepoint,Google G Suite,Lotus 123,Lotus Notes,Filenet;
• OS: Windows,macOS,Linux;
• Image: Adobe Photoshop,Adobe Lightroom,Autocad.

projects.description:
Public Sector Entity: Study of the national market of document management and physical archive, to identify the go no-go for investment in this market by the entity:
•	Market Analysis (competitors, market shares, potential customers, potential products and services, characterisation of current technological status and their trends, logistics and transportation, etc.);
•	Evaluation of technological solutions concerning the Outsourcing of document management;
•	Economic and financial analysis of the project (viability analysis, sensitivity analysis, "Goodwill" that partners could bring to the business);
•	Evaluation of the ability of obtaining incentives to support project (QREN).

Design and implementation of an e-Gov System, supported in an application of Court Case Management of Filenet (Document Management and Workflow), for management of digital processes in Administrative and Tax courts:
•	Web-enabled application installed in 19 courts;
•	Definition of the architecture, the infrastructure and the governance model;
•	Certification of documents with personal digital signature;
•	Procedural workflow with management of deadlines and alerts online;
•	User Authentication with digital certificates;
•	Developments in .Net, HTML, SQL Server 2000, Filenet, Neevia and Power Designer;
•	Interoperability with systems of other agencies;
•	Administration of the system, network and infrastructure.

